A woman is fighting for her life after becoming a human torch when she apparently set herself on fire inside a Scottish police station.

Horrified officers rushed to douse the flames which one eye witness said engulfed the woman's body at Clydebank Police Station in West Dunbartonshire.

Fire crews raced to the scene and an ambulance took the woman to the Glasgow Royal Infirmary, where she is said to be in a critical condition.

