'I thought it was a practice thing, because it was outside the police station.

'There were people walking by and cars were slowing down, but no one stopped to help at the time.'

One local resident, who did not want to be named, also told of how they saw fire engines and ambulances race to the scene.

He said: I saw police officers coming out of the police station itself, maybe three or four officers, maybe more.

'And next thing they stopped. I don’t know if the person collapsed or something like that.

'After that the fire brigade were there first and after that ambulances arrived.

'It’s the kind of thing you expect to see on TV, not here.'

Meanwhile on Twitter, the Scottish Police Federation wrote: 'Horrific incident at Clydebank police station.

